The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to solve the problem of prominent object detection and recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new problem formulation and method to achieve the task, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method involves deep learning models, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the potential improvements in emulating bio-inspired vision systems, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in assistive vision, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
